JDS Uniphase Shares Get Boost From Agilent’s Rosy Outlook

-- B y   I a n   K i n g
-- 
2011-03-04T22:19:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/jds-uniphase-shares-get-boost-from-agilent-s-rosy-outlook-1-.html
  JDS Uniphase Corp. (JDSU)  shares jumped
8.9 percent after  Agilent Technologies Inc. (A)  gave a bullish
outlook for the test-and-measurement market, JDS’s biggest
source of revenue.  The shares rose $2.23 to $27.37 at 4 p.m. New York time on
the Nasdaq Stock Market, the biggest one-day gain since Feb. 11.
The shares have climbed 89 percent this year.  The Milpitas, California-based company makes machinery that
tests whether network equipment is working properly. Agilent,
the largest test-and-measurement company, yesterday told
analysts that market growth is holding up.  “All the evidence suggests that growth that we say in our
first quarter is continuing,” said Agilent Chief Executive
Officer Bill Sullivan. The Santa Clara, California-based company
reported sales growth of 25 percent in the three months ended
Jan. 31.  Agilent shares also rose, gaining $3.93, or 9.2 percent, to
$46.75 on the New York Stock Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
